We could also use a showAnnotations() call, but this had better padding behavior and can be customized depending on the layout of the other cards.

Classes/EditViewController.html.name: EditViewController
Classes/EditViewController.html.abstract: The EditViewController becomes a child UIViewController of the PlaceDetailsController. It manages all components and functions related to editing a timeline entry.

Classes/TimelineEntry.html.name: TimelineEntry
Classes/TimelineEntry.html.abstract: The TimelineEntry object references a start and end time, a movement time, and a label for the place in the timeline UI.

Classes/MainViewController.html.name: MainViewController
Classes/MainViewController.html.abstract: MainViewController object manages the layout and views for the entire application. In addition to the mapView, date label, and timelineView, it manages a child PlaceDetailsController (which has an additional child UIViewController for editing the place).

Classes/Style.html.name: Style
Classes/Style.html.abstract: Class containing all style constants for Phind, including colors, offsets, and shadow parameters.

Classes/Util.html.name: Util
Classes/Util.html.abstract: All the utility / helper functions can be found here, including date formatting and conversion.

Classes/RawCoordinates.html.name: RawCoordinates
Classes/RawCoordinates.html.abstract: The RawCoordinates object is the lowest level information collected from the user through CoreMotion. It includes a latitude, longitude, movement type, and timestamp (as well as an auto-generated UUID).

Classes/LocationEntry.html.name: LocationEntry
Classes/LocationEntry.html.abstract: The LocationEntry class is one level removed from the RawCoordinates; it stores a collection of RawCoordinates as well as a central latitude and longitude for the given set of coordinates. It also manages a start and end time, as well as a movement type for the set of entries.

Classes/Place.html.name: Place
Classes/Place.html.abstract: The Place object stores information from external sources, such as the Google Maps API. Different location entries may correspond to the same place object, which includes an address, name, and 2D coordinate location.

Classes/MapPin.html.name: MapPin
Classes/MapPin.html.abstract: The MapPin object can be added as an annotation to a MapView; it stores an individual coordinate, title, and subtitle.

Classes/TimelineUITableViewCell.html.name: TimelineUITableViewCell
Classes/TimelineUITableViewCell.html.abstract: The TimelineUITableViewCell stores the requisite UI components for displaying the timeline value to the user, including a label, image, duration, and time.

Classes/PhotoCell.html.name: PhotoCell
Classes/PhotoCell.html.abstract: The PhotoCell encapsulates a single photo used to display place details.
